Abstract = {Based on insights into the nature of vocational mathematical knowledge,
   we designed a computer tool with which students in laboratory schools at
   senior secondary vocational school level could develop a better
   proficiency in the proportional reasoning involved in dilution. We did
   so because we had identified computations of concentrations of chemical
   substances after dilution as a problematic area in the vocational
   education of laboratory technicians. Pre- and post-test results indeed
   show that 47 students aged 16-23 significantly improved their
   proportional reasoning in this domain with brief instruction time (50-90
   min). Effect sizes were mostly large. The approach of using a visual
   tool that foregrounds mathematical aspects of laboratory work thus
   illustrates how vocational mathematical knowledge can be developed
   effectively and efficiently.},
