Month = {JAN},
Abstract = {Researchers have argued teachers and students are not developing
   connected meanings for function inverse, thus calling for a closer
   examination of teachers' and students' inverse function meanings.
   Responding to this call, we characterize 25 pre-service teachers'
   inverse function meanings as inferred from our analysis of clinical
   interviews. After summarizing relevant research, we describe the
   methodology and theoretical framework we used to interpret the
   pre-service teachers' activities. We then present data highlighting the
   techniques the pre-service teachers used when responding to tasks that
   involved analytical and graphical representations of functions and
   inverse functions in both decontextualized and contextualized situations
   and discuss our inferences of their meanings based on their activities.
   We conclude with implications for the teaching and learning of inverse
   function and areas for future research.},
